{{Infobox writing system |type=[[pictographic]] |typedesc=and [[syllabary|syllabic]] |name=''Dongba'' and ''geba'' |languages = [[Naxi language|Naxi]] |time = 1000 CE ? to present |sample = Painted Naxi panel.jpeg |note = none }} The [[Naxi language]] of southwestern [[China]] may be written in the syllabic [[geba syllabary|''geba'' script]]. There is also a Naxi tradition of pictographic symbols called [[Dongba symbols|''dongba'']]; this may sometimes be [[Interlinear gloss|gloss]]ed with ''geba'' for clarification, since a ''dongba'' text may be intelligible only to its author.
A [[Latin script|Latin alphabet]] was developed for Naxi in the 20th century. {| |+ align=bottom| ''Facing pages of a Naxi manuscript, displaying both pictographic ''dongba'' and smaller syllabic ''geba.'' | [[Image:Naxi manuscript (left) 2087.jpg|237px]]||[[Image:Naxi manuscript (right) 2088.jpg|244px]] |}
